Metro officer Henry Motene is the Daily Sun Sunhero. Motene helped a woman who was stranded at Wemmer Pan Road on
Tuesday. It is understood the woman was on her way to fetch her
daughter from school, when she ran out of petrol. She said her petrol gauge was not functional when the
officer pulled off. Motene drove her to the nearest petrol station and paid for
her petrol before driving her back to her car. According to the woman, Motene was concerned about her
safety as the area had several crime incidents. 